
<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>
Microsoft Office Excel provide enhanced conditional formatting support from Excel 2007 onwards. Conditional formatting allows you to apply formatting to one or more cells based on the value of the cell or the value of a formula.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
XlsIO also supports applying more than three conditional formats to a single cell in XLSX format, whereas XLS format allows only three conditional formats in a cell.
</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Apply conditional formats to a range of cells</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Advanced options of Excel, such as color scales, icon sets and data bars</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Format unique and duplicate values in single line</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

